<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-06-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="958" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Johnson Electoral Mission/204:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-03T14:00:00-04:00">June 3, 1931—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>129. Legation’s 91, May 29, 3 p.m. Please report by telegraph whether the
                            National Board of Elections of Nicaragua normally functions in
                            connection with municipal elections and has jurisdiction over same. If
                            so, explain fully to what extent and cite appropriate laws.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>